cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with video analysis and activity detection using neural networks. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses different architectures and configurations tested to achieve the best performance and learning of the video dataset provided. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing and processing video data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to classify and temporally localize activities in videos. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper uses recurrent neural networks for activity detection.
